::Striker::

Striker stops, looking down a cliff. In front of him and Spears stretched the 
valley that he had been heading to. It was covered with grass, trees rising 
(can you believe I missed a point on a Precalt quiz because I misspelled 
"rise"??) from the ground, providing shade and a calm feeling. On either 
side, hills rose, cooling it down, and giving it more shade.

The place looked beautiful.

"Well, dear," he says to Spears, "How do you like it?"
